ur people out of Relentless pleading with them to give my folks a chance to get to the lair. Told them several times I had forces in route. Folks that gave up other camps they were in to come and assist me. The responses I got from Relentless people I spoke with was a direct no. Followed by speak with so and so. I did. Again a flat "sorry, no deal. We're killing him."<P>Sunday night was the worst night I have had in ages. I felt I was completely disrespected and I vowed never to assist TR in anything again. Monday, apologies were made to folks other than myself, and offers of assistance came about to others than to myself. <P>My question is, how are clerics like me suppose to be able to get ragefire after wasting an entire day sitting there for nothing when another guild comes in like this and has no thoughts about at least ASKING if that cleric has the forces coming to assist? If I had not had my friends from other guilds able to assist me, I would have stepped out of the lair long before midnight that night. As it was, I did have folks to aid me and he was snatched out from under me.<P>It's been two days since this happened and I am not the type of person to hold personal grudges for long. But I will tell you that after this happened, I do not ever see me completing this quest.<P><BR>------------------<BR>Areia Shadowleaf<BR>Lady of the Guild of Albion<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Grombar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Well i have 2 bad flings with zordak, first was a call that zord was up along with naggy, yes both naggy and zord where up, so a newbie group was taking naggy down, while they where buffing my guild pulled 3 groups there to take zord down, meanwhile another guild showd up saying zord was taken and that the naggy raid was also taking zord for the other guild, ended in rolloff that i lost due to the random 100 ending up with a 0, bah that suckd, other one was yesterday for, started clearing fgs to set up camp early in the morning, zord spawnd with 5 fgs left, 2 guilds where there looking for zord, in 10 mins 3 more guilds showd, in the end someone spawnd zord and everyone ended up killing him, guy got lucky and got his epic, 4 other clerics walked away pissed.<P>Grombar Kegdrainer<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Viscera</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Happened to a fellow guildee of mine. I wasn't there, but heard about it, and will make this as objective as possible.<P>Friend was camping in Sol B, not sure where, either at SS room, or Naggy's Lair when Ragefire spawned. It was about 6-10 people that were clearing the FG's every 6 hrs, for about two days now, so there was no question who was camping it. Ragefire spawned early in the morning, so the call for reinforcements was going to be tough. About the same time, another guild, more suited to the hour, brought in many groups to "steal" Ragefire.<P>Arguments abound as to who had the "rights" to the spawn. With many warnings as to what would happen if the bigger guild intervened (our guild would kill the merchant, yes I know, was stupid in retrospect), the other guild refused to back down. Unfortunately, no one received their epic that day, and our cleric quit the game for a few weeks, very close to forever.<P>This was back in December, and I know the situation has gone drastically downhill since then. Even when I got my epic in January, everyone respected the campers. For the most part on my server, the campers are respected, but it only takes one bunch of idiots to blow it all.<P>------------------<BR>Viscera Galen<BR>L60 High Priest of Brell<BR><A HREF="http://members.home.net/wire23" TARGET=_blank>Black Tower</A><BR>Xegony</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Georgia_TKR</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">About three weeks ago my guild, T`Kagi Ro, on Fennin Ro decided to start helping our second cleric get her epic. We had worked really hard to get her the pearl and she had held it for a month before we thought we would give Ragefire a second go. The first time we had done Ragefire without any issues. We ran up and just took him. This time, however, we had severe issues.<P>Quite a few clerics, over 100 to be exact, on Fennin Ro have been attempting to nab Ragefire for a long time. My guild had been clearing Fire Giants all week long and a few guilds whom I am friends with were very cordial and stepped out of the Ragefire scene while we tried to get our epic finished and go. <P>Ragefire spawned. We were screaming in guildchat for everyone to rush to Solusek B so we could kill him and get this epic out of the way. We had had long, hard hours put into this camp and we were ready for it to end. Alas, not 2 minutes after we said Ragefire was up did Defenders of Akanon (DoA) ran up and a few of their members said that we did not deserve the spawn because we were not an "uber" guild. They announced that they were taking the dragon because we were obviously not ready to handle him... obviously they felt that 30+ players over level 50 were not good enough to take the dragon. We were assembled and ready to go. We needed only to make our groups. They refused to wait for a GM to arrive on the scene and turned in the pearl. They killed the dragon, then one of our rogues ran up and power looted the dragon's loot and ran off with it. <P>Fighting was like nothing I had ever seen before. It turned out that the DoA cleric, Celex (a former member of my own guild who left for loot), had left an alternate character guilded in T`kagi Ro. She logged onto this character to look at our guildchat... to see when Ragefire was spawning, etc. That is how her new guild, her uber guild, knew when to rush to Solusek B and steal Ragefire from beneath our feet. <P>Our rogue was merely suspended for a week. Their cleric, well, unfortunately she was given the heart back by the GM not three days later. <P>This happens every single time Ragefire spawns. There are sometimes three to four monks or rogues camping in Nagafen's Chamber. If Nagafen is up, everything is on hold til a smaller guild can run in and kill him. Guilds have been fighting more and more over the past 2 weeks since the incident occured. People have been so hateful and spiteful towards others... I myself have lost several friends from the opposing guilds from this incident. <P>What is epic? Is having this rare spawn epic? No. Why can't he be like Ixiblat Fer? Triggerable during specific hours? Why does he have to be in Solusek A? Why can't they just put him out in Lavastorm? They fixed the bards... they fixed the druids and the rangers... they fixed the necromancers... now what about us? Why are they ignoring almost every email and comment sent to them regarding this horrible spawn? That's a question I hope they can answer if they ever read this far into this thread that you send them Rayne.<P>------------------<BR>Georgia Gaelicmyst<BR>Cleric of Tunare<BR>Everlore Staff Member<BR>http://www.everlore.com/</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dalur - Veeshan</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Here's my Ragefire incident:<P>I had been camping in Naggy's lair since Sunday.<P>Logged in monday night - no<BR>                         FG's and no ragefire. Spent 5 hours sitting in his lair.<P>                         Tuesday log in - some anon FD monk sitting off to the side where ragefire would normally spawn. Give him a couple tells nothing.<BR>                         Then Magus Rokyl spawns and forces me out of the zone. Get a couple groups and clear out the FG's. Groups sit with me for 45<BR>                         mins, no ragefire spawn, so they leave and I camp out.<P>                         Wednesday log in - FG's are up and I get chased out of the zone by a fire giant wizard. Call for backup and get ready to go beat up on<BR>                         the FG's, another guild rushes past us and starts beating on the FG's. I wait till they finish then wander up to Naggy's lair and camp<BR>                         out.<P>                         Thursday log in - no FG's and no ragefire. Couple guild mates are in Sol B doing bats and bugs. One of them pulls a body for me to<BR>                         res. I res the body and they go about their way. I notice the same FD monk that was there since tuesday. I proceed to walk around<BR>                         his FD body a couple times and then stand ontop of him and jump and do a few other funny things; no response.<P>                         Then I go and sit back in the corner with the camera view set so I can see where ragefire spawns and down the path towards the<BR>                         drawbridge.<P>                         I'm sitting there and suddenly I see a figure with a red robe and a stick kinda fall from the ceiling. I proceed to walk over and inspect<BR>                         the figure - named Zhordak Ragefire. I right click him and am present with a vendor menu. I immediately do a /GU GET TO SOL B -<BR>                         RAGEFIRE IS UP!!!<P>                         Shortly thereafter, the 2 guildies are sitting near ragefire. 1 other guildmate that was in lavastorm comes rushing in and there are 4 of<BR>                         us. Another 5 mins passes and I see the FD monk sit up and camp out. No word about this is camped or so forth.<P>                         A few mins later another group of my guildies show up and we start forming groups.<P>                         2 mins later, 3 groups of the FD's monk rush in and start buffing. Needless to say, they ended up getting more groups inside than we<BR>                         did and they spawned Ragefire with all of us sitting in the lair.<P>------------------<BR>Dalur Stouthealer<BR